org.mundo.filter
Class ActiveMapFilter

java.lang.Object
  org.mundo.rt.TypedContainer
      org.mundo.rt.ActiveMap
          org.mundo.filter.ActiveMapFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>, IFilter, IFilterConstants, IActivate, ICopy
public final class ActiveMapFilter
extends ActiveMap
implements IFilter

A ActiveMapFilter holds a set of attribute filters to be evaluated against passive ActiveMaps.

Author:
Erwin Aitenbichler

Method Detail

toString

public java.lang.String toString()
Returns a string representation of this filter. The string representation consists of a list of key-value mappings in the order returned by the map's entrySet view's iterator, enclosed in braces ("{}"). The active class name is printed, if it is set, followed by a colon (":"). Adjacent mappings are separated by the characters ", " (comma and space). Each key-value mapping is rendered as the key followed by an equals sign ("=") followed by the associated value.

Overrides:
toString in class ActiveMap
See Also:
Object.toString()

putByte

public void putByte(java.lang.String key,
                    byte value)
Defines an attribute filter with operator OP_EQUAL and comparison value value to be evaluated against the attribute named key. If the map previously contained a mapping for key, the old mapping is replaced regardless of the previous type. The filter is internally stored using the IntegerAttributeFilter class.
